<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="G" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Grasp2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Grasp,</orth> vb. to gripe, to seize: <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.97" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B V, 1, 97</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.5.132" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 5, 132</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 3, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.12.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 12, 46</bibl>. <cit><quote>with his arms outstretched --s in the comer,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 3.3.168" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 3, 168</bibl></cit>. Absol. == to grapple, to strive, to struggle: <cit><quote>one that --ed and tugged for life,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.172" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 172</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>